Conan Edogawa Poe

  • child of Ranpo [Edogawa] and Edgar Allan [Poe] Edogawa Poe
    • oldest child of its family
  • Genderfloren transfem, nonbinary
    • it/its
  • demiromantic abrosexual
  • starts the series at 13 and ends at 20
  • born April 25th, 2001
  • Namesake: Arthur Conan Doyle
  • Ability: Sherlock Holmes
    • Ability Details: Conan’s ability, Sherlock Holmes, allows for Conan to transfer any amount of knowledge it stores in its memory to someone else by touching them on the head with its right hand and saying “I wish to share.” Once the memory is transferred, Conan no longer has control over it, and cannot remember it unless reminded of it by an outside source (it is for this reason that Conan carries a notebook everywhere it goes), or until the new holder of the memory returns it to Conan by touching it with their left hand and saying “I wish to return.”
  • Affiliation: primarily known for being a member within The Hateful Eight, a founding member of the Gunslinger Kids; it is also one of the first members of the Apprentices of the ADA, and later on one of the first second gen kids to join the ADA in full
  • Level at which I think about them: high; it's a main character in THE HATEFUL EIGHT after all, and also it's just such a cool little creature
  • Brief Notes:
    • An upbeat and energetic, kind soul, Conan is absolutely a bright shining jewel in its family and in its friend group. Despite its hardships in life (Conan has ADHD, autism, and also has suffered from chronic migraines and insomnia ever since it was young), one would never guess Conan has any worries at all when they first meet thanks to how carefree and sweet it is. Conan genuinely believes humanity is the most beautiful thing on Earth, and enjoys spending time simply observing the people around it. As a child, Conan was bullied quite badly due to its “odd” behavior by other children (and sometimes by teachers as well), but it was quickly aided by the Tiger Twins (Murasaki and Nobunori Nakajima-Akutagawa), who became some of its first friends (and, in Nobunori’s case, its first crush/romantic attraction).
    • Conan is extremely intelligent and intuitive, much like both of its fathers, however it is far more outgoing, talkative, and friendly than either of its fathers. Where Ranpo’s main flaw lies in his childish behavior, Conan is not so much childish as it is naive and unaware of the concept of anyone wanting to take advantage of it, or use its ability for their own personal gain. It relates more to Ranpo than Edgar, but that is not to say it is not like Edgar at all; while Conan prefers not to get violent, it does not condemn violence either when perpetrated by others against the proper targets (not innocent people). It was also taught extensively in self-defense by its grandfather, Yukichi Fukuzawa, and its aunt, Akiko Yosano-Ozaki. Its self-proclaimed Uncle Francis Fitzgerald also helped to teach it how to protect itself whenever he came to visit in the past, and now that all the members of the Guild are living in Yokohama again, he and it have quite the bond and relationship, much to its parents’ chagrin.
